    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Cylinder Head and Valve Train - Cleaning,
        Inspection, and Testing - Valves
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s10.3.5" svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Valves</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a wire brush to remove all carbon from valve stems and heads.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect each valve. Replace valves having burn marks, warping, scuffing, bending or valve
                tip spalling.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure each valve stem diameter for wear using a 0-1 inch micrometer. Measure valves at
                three locations 90&#176; apart. Replace valves with stem diameter less than minimum valve stem diameter
                specification. See
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_235.xml" xrefid="s10.t1">Specifications</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s10.t1"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3450010058" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figM08/M08174.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Measurement of valve face margin</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, maintain a minimum valve face margin across the entire valve face. An
                    insufficient margin will not provide correct heat dissipation, leading to valve warping or breakage.
                    Replace valve if margin is less than specification. See
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_235.xml" xrefid="s10.t1">Specifications</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s10.t1"/>.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a dial caliper to measure valve face margin at four locations (90&#176; apart).</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
